TITLE: Israeli protesters demand Gaza cease-fire in rare anti-war march through Tel Aviv
SUMMARY: Civil rights lawyers pushed back against a crackdown on protests, securing permission to hold a rally to stop the war in Gaza.

TITLE: Charcuterie sold at Costco and Sam's Club is being linked to a salmonella outbreak
SUMMARY: The CDC says there have been at least 47 illnesses across 22 states tied to the outbreak, which officials believe is linked to charcuterie meat trays sold at the two wholesale stores.

TITLE: Jack Burke Jr., who was the oldest living Masters champion, dies at age 100
SUMMARY: In 1956, Burke staged the greatest comeback ever at Augusta National. He was a member of the World Golf Hall of Fame, won the PGA Championship and was equally skilled as a teacher.

TITLE: Los Angeles Innocence Project takes Scott Peterson's case, decades after conviction
SUMMARY: This week, Peterson's legal team filed motions seeking evidence and DNA testing. They're the first new court filings in his murder case in a year.

TITLE: Jordan accuses Israel of deliberately targeting its Gaza field hospital
SUMMARY: Jordan said its field hospital in Khan Younis was hit by shells and gunfire, injuring a doctor and a patient. Israel denied the claim and said it was engaged in a skirmish with Hamas fighters nearby.

TITLE: Boeing 747 cargo plane with reported engine trouble makes emergency landing in Miami
SUMMARY: A plane flown by Atlas Air experienced an engine malfunction and made an emergency landing at Miami International Airport shortly after takeoff. A witness said she saw sparks shooting from the plane.

TITLE: Up First briefing: Congress averts shutdown again; DOJ report details Uvalde failures
SUMMARY: Congress passed a stopgap bill to fund the government through early March and avert a shutdown. The Justice Department details "cascading failures" in the police response to the Uvalde shooting.

TITLE: A rising tide of infrastructure funding floats new hope for Great Lakes shipping
SUMMARY: Trains and trucks move the bulk of goods across the U.S. Some sailors say the Great Lakes waterways are underused shipping options and hope $17 billion of federal investment can help revitalize them.

TITLE: A Chinese and a Taiwanese comedian walk into a bar ...
SUMMARY: Taiwanese comedian Vickie Wang and Chinese comedian Jamie Wang work through the lived experience of cross-strait tensions through comedy.

TITLE: German government wants companies to 'de-risk' from China, but business is reluctant
SUMMARY: Tough new rhetoric on China from some members of Germany's governing coalition has led to disagreement rather than unity on what the government's policy should be.

TITLE: 'Cozy' relationship between Boeing and the U.S. draws scrutiny amid 737 Max 9 mess
SUMMARY: The latest safety lapse at Boeing renews concerns about the company's influence in Washington, and whether federal regulators have delegated too much of their oversight authority to its employees.

TITLE: Harris is taking the lead on gun violence prevention. Will she reach young people?
SUMMARY: Vice President Harris has been holding events at the White House and around the country on gun violence prevention. It's part of an effort to reach young voters and voters of color.

TITLE: Iran's regional flashpoints are increasing. Here's what to know
SUMMARY: Pakistan and Iran have traded cross-border rocket attacks, stoking fears of widening conflict even farther.

TITLE: Driven to distraction: New rules limit those humorous state highway signs
SUMMARY: The Federal Highway Administration tells states to cut back on word play that can confuse drivers.

TITLE: From things that suck to stars that shine â€” it's the weekly news quiz
SUMMARY: This week, we saw the Iowa caucuses suck up news coverage, an ancient space entity suck in stars, and low temps suck the charge from Teslas. Were you paying attention?
